  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>I will mentor someone else to do this, happily.

Dealing with Hudson isn't all that difficult, and this would be hugely helpful.
If you want to do this, the first step is to find me and request an account on
Hudson. (-:

You can read <a href="http://openhatch.org/wiki/Continuous_integration_with_Hudson">http://openhatch.org/wiki/Continuous_integration_with_Hudson</a> for
more info.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg1261">msg1261 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: paulproteus</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-03-14.15:26:25</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Right now, Hudson tests if the code on origin/master works.

It would also be good if it tested this: "If a new contributor downloaded the
code, and ran the migrations, would it work?"

(The migrations have long been a sticking point, where there are problems but I
(Asheesh) don't notice in any reasonable amount of time.)</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
